I.e. here we have:

    typedef struct tx_sem sem_t;

Then in sem_posix.c, have:

    #include "tx_api.h"

    struct tx_sem { TX_SEMAPHORE txsem; };

Best practice would be:

- Replace with LE_MUTEX_DECLARE_REF(), or
- Lock/Unlock should be function-like macros, and not include the trailing semi-colon.  This makes them look more like regular C code and avoids unexpected behaviour for things like:

    if (foo)
        LOCK;
    else   //< compiler error here.
        // throw error

